    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) that serves as a benchmark for the golden era of JDM engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW twin-rotor power plant, featuring the sophisticated sequential turbocharging system that delivers a seamless transition through the power band. The chassis is structurally immaculate, maintaining the factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution and aluminum double-wishbone suspension for surgical handling precision. Recent diagnostic testing confirms exceptional compression across all rotor faces, well within original factory tolerances. Every component, from the Torsen limited-slip differential to the vacuum-controlled solenoids, remains in peak operational status. Finished in its factory Montego Blue Mica with a pristine interior and a documented service history, this unmolested survivor represents a rare opportunity for the discerning rotary purist.",
